:: About [frame] {"position":"225,624","size":"100,100"}
//Let Us Be Weightless// is truly an interactive short story. What you have in front of you is part one, which was first conceived in response to the //Material Conditions 1// small art challenge, launched by salt.codes and supported by the Immersive Realities Labs for the humanities (irlHumanities). <br>

When I received my crowdsourced creation prompt, I was in the middle of teaching my //Deep Time: Memory, Media, and Ecological Imagination in the Americas// course. My prompt inspired me to rethink what we know about modern technological formations, particularly given my course's emphasis on identifying and attending to the diverse ecologics of people of color in the Americas. <br>

